%3Cli%3ELucas%20Da%20Silva%20leads%20a%20team%20of%20five%20window%20cleaners%20for%20the%20Leadenhall%20skyscraper%20in%20London.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20takes%20the%20team%20six%20months%20to%20clean%20the%20entire%20building%2C%20and%20then%20they%20immediately%20start%20again.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDa%20Silva%20said%20he%20thought%20he%20would%20die%20the%20first%20time%20he%20went%20up%20the%20skyscraper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Lucas%20Da%20Silva%2C%20a%20vertical%20site%20supervisor%20for%20the%20Leadenhall%20Building%20in%20London.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20went%20up%20the%20Leadenhall%20Building%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20224.5%20meters%20tall%2C%20or%20about%20738%20feet%20%E2%80%94%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20going%20to%20die.%20I%20wasn't%20ready%20for%20the%20height.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20see%20the%20tiny%20people%20down%20on%20the%20street%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20my%20soul%20leave%20my%20body%20and%20come%20back%20again.%20The%20sensation%20was%20terrible.%20I%20started%20to%20question%20myself%3A%20%26quot%3BDid%20I%20choose%20the%20right%20job%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20Brazilian%20and%20have%20lived%20in%20the%20UK%20since%202013.%20I%20started%20working%20as%20a%20toilet%20cleaner%2C%20and%20I%20would%20see%20the%20window-cleaning%20guys%20hanging%20outside.%20I%20decided%20that%20one%20day%20I%20would%20do%20that%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22822%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20skyscraper%20window%20washer%20in%20the%20cradle.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6565af4bfd6200867dd01007%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221294%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDa%20Silva%20in%20the%20cradle%20washing%20the%20Leadenhall%20Building.%3Cp%3ELucas%20Da%20Silva%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20738-foot%20Leadenhall%20is%20the%20tallest%20building%20I've%20cleaned%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20never%20been%20up%20that%20high%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20explore%20my%20limits.%20I%20was%20told%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20speak%20better%20English%20first.%20I%20put%20myself%20to%20English%20classes%2C%20and%20in%202017%2C%20I%20joined%20the%20window%20cleaning%20team%20at%205%20Broadgate.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20formal%20training%20%E2%80%94%20you%20learn%20on%20the%20job%20and%20gain%20experience.%20It%20takes%20about%20a%20year%20to%20become%20a%20window%20cleaner.%20I've%20continued%20my%20studies%2C%20and%20I'm%20about%20to%20finish%20my%20level%205%20BTEC%20%E2%80%94%20a%20specialist%20work-related%20qualification%20%E2%80%94%20and%20start%20a%20degree%20in%20public%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20Advance%20Cleaning%20in%20December%202022.%20Since%20May%2C%20I've%20been%20in%20charge%20of%20window%20cleaning%20at%20the%20Leadenhall%20Building%20and%20have%20a%20team%20of%20five%20people%20working%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20building%20is%20unique%3A%20Each%20floor%20was%20designed%20to%20be%20narrower%20than%20the%20one%20below%20to%20avoid%20obscuring%20views%20of%20St%20Paul's%20Cathedral.%20We%20have%20three%20different%20cradles%20that%20have%20been%20specially%20designed%20to%20clean%20the%20windows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cradles%20are%20baskets%20suspended%20from%20the%20top%20of%20the%20building%20by%20wires.%20They%20are%20held%20to%20the%20building%20with%20sockets%2C%20so%20we're%20protected%20if%20the%20wind%20changes.%20We%20wear%20harnesses%20inside%20the%20cradle%20but%20never%20leave%20the%20basket%20%E2%80%94%20we%20care%20about%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECleaning%20skyscrapers%20is%20a%20slow%20and%20logistically%20complex%20operation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20window-cleaning%20shifts%20start%20at%2010%3A30%20p.m.%20and%20finish%20at%202%20p.m.%20the%20next%20day.%20Two%20of%20my%20team%20work%20overnight%2C%20from%2010%3A30%20p.m.%20to%206%3A30%20a.m.%2C%20and%20three%20work%20during%20the%20day%2C%20from%20about%206%20a.m.%20until%202%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEach%20cradle%20can%20hold%20four%20cleaners%20who%20can%20access%20two%20vertical%20windows%20at%20a%20time.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EWe%20start%20from%20the%20top%20of%20the%20building%20with%20the%20cradle%20and%20clean%20that%20column%20of%20windows%20in%20a%20vertical%20strip%20all%20the%20way%20down.%20We%20call%20this%20a%20%26quot%3Bdrop.%26quot%3B%20In%20good%20weather%20conditions%2C%20it%20takes%20about%20a%20day%20and%20a%20half%20to%20do%20one%20drop.%20If%20it's%20windy%2C%20it'll%20take%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20starting%20a%20new%20drop%2C%20we%20check%20the%20wind%20direction%20and%20position%20the%20cradle%20at%20the%20best%20part%20of%20the%20building%20to%20clean%2C%20not%20necessarily%20the%20next%20section.%20We%20take%20before-and-after%20pictures%20and%20use%20an%20online%20system%20to%20track%20our%20drops%20so%20I%20can%20see%20exactly%20what%20parts%20of%20the%20building%20need%20to%20be%20cleaned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20takes%206%20months%20to%20clean%20the%20whole%20building%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20then%20you%20immediately%20start%20again%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20about%20six%20months%20to%20clean%20the%20whole%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20you%20finish%20one%20side%2C%20you%20start%20again.%20You%20never%20stop.%20Last%20year%2C%20we%20were%20about%20to%20finish%20the%20building%20when%20we%20got%20hit%20by%20the%20Sahara%20dust%20storm%2C%20which%20made%20all%20the%20windows%20dirty%20again.%20We%20started%20again%20the%20next%20day.%20It's%20endless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20part%20of%20window%20cleaning%20is%20working%20with%20the%20weather.%20We%20don't%20go%20out%20if%20the%20wind%20is%20over%2015%20miles%20an%20hour.%20If%20we're%20out%20on%20the%20cradle%20and%20we%20feel%20the%20wind%20changing%2C%20we'll%20check%20the%20conditions%20with%20an%20anemometer.%20If%20we%20can't%20continue%2C%20we%20take%20the%20cradle%20back%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20never%20get%20used%20to%20the%20risks%20of%20working%20that%20high%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221106%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lucas%20Da%20Silva%2C%20a%20window%20washer%20stood%20inside%20the%20Leadenhall%20Building.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6565b00ec58b6f84123ad498%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221350%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDa%20Silva%20admires%20the%20view%20from%20the%20top%20floors%20of%20Leadenhall%20Building.%20%3Cp%3ELucas%20Da%20Silva%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHealth%20and%20safety%20applies%20to%20every%20aspect%20of%20this%20job.%20It%20takes%20an%20hour%20at%20the%20beginning%20and%20end%20of%20each%20day%20to%20inspect%20our%20equipment%2C%20take%20pictures%2C%20and%20input%20everything%20into%20our%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20we%20get%20the%20cradle%20out%2C%20we%20mark%20out%20an%20exclusion%20zone%20below%20in%20case%20something%20falls%3A%20a%20squeegee%2C%20clothes%2C%20gloves%20%E2%80%94%20even%20dirty%20water%2C%20which%20can%20stain%20clothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20out%20there%20on%20the%20facade%2C%20the%20wind%20can%20pick%20up%20at%20any%20moment%2C%20and%20the%20gusts%20are%20unpredictable.%20The%20tall%20buildings%20on%20Bishopsgate%2C%20the%20street%20next%20door%2C%20create%20a%20wind%20tunnel%2C%20and%20the%20wind%20gains%20speed%20when%20it%20hits%20the%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20time%2C%20we%20came%20out%20with%20the%20cradle%20and%20a%20gust%20hit%20us%20from%20below.%20We%20felt%20the%20cradle%20flying.%20It's%20scary%20because%20it's%20not%20in%20your%20control.%20You%20never%20get%20used%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20son%20thinks%20I'm%20brave%20and%20it%20makes%20me%20proud%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%2013-year-old%20son%20thinks%20I'm%20the%20bravest%20person%20in%20the%20world.%20My%20friends%20say%20they'd%20never%20do%20this%20job%20themselves.%20Being%20told%20that%20I'm%20brave%20makes%20me%20believe%20it%2C%20and%20when%20I%20wake%20up%20early%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20it%20encourages%20me%20to%20go%20the%20extra%20mile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20loved%20ones%20know%20where%20I've%20come%20from%20and%20where%20I%20am%20now.%20They%20see%20my%20resilience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20waves%20when%20they%20see%20us%2C%20even%20in%20the%20building%20next%20door.%20We%20wave%20back%20or%20we%20draw%20a%20smiley%20face%20on%20the%20window%20with%20soap.%20It's%20nice%20%E2%80%94%20we%20know%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20most%20people%2C%20they're%20just%20windows%2C%20but%20we%20look%20closely%20at%20every%20pane%20of%20glass.%20I%20enjoy%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20job%20and%20the%20details.%20When%20I%20see%20the%20glass%20shine%2C%20I%20feel%20proud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20view%20from%20the%20top%20is%20like%20nothing%20I've%20seen%20before.%20You%20can%20see%20everything%3A%20the%20river%2C%20Tower%20Bridge%2C%20the%20Tower%20of%20London.%20Being%20up%20there%20and%20looking%20at%20the%20city%20gives%20me%20a%20sense%20of%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskyscraper-window-cleaner-washer-what-job-like-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701166895000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6564b0c5fe5bc6545ebc5615%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskyscraper-window-cleaner-washer-what-job-like-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20skyscraper%20window%20washer%20shares%20how%20he%20cleans%20a%20740-foot%20high-rise%20in%20London.%20He's%20always%20aware%20of%20the%20job's%20risks%20but%20says%20it%20makes%20him%20feel%20free.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider