2Fa%3E%20is%20increasingly%20uncomfortable%20with%20yuan%20trade%2C%20since%20there%20are%20currency%20conversion%20charges%20involved%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdedollarization-china-india-brics-common-currency-jim-oneill-economy-dollar-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egeopolitical%20rivalry%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20Delhi%20and%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20currency%20Russia%20could%20use%20to%20trade%20with%20India%20is%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20dirham%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20UAE%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-11-23%2Fuae-tightens-scrutiny-on-russian-firms-amid-pressure-from-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasing%20its%20oversight%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Russian%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20all%20the%20risks%20and%20complications%20that%20come%20with%20trading%20in%20alternatives%20to%20the%20US%20dollar%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20is%20not%20backing%20off%20its%20stance%20to%20move%20away%20from%20dollar%20trades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20all%20the%20problems%20with%20the%20rupee%2C%20we%20nevertheless%20prefer%20trading%20in%20rupees%20and%20rubles%20and%20not%20in%20dollars.%20This%20already%20speaks%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20have%20excluded%20the%20option%20of%20dollarization%20in%20our%20bilateral%20trade%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sergey%20Ivanov%2C%20a%20senior%20Russian%20official%20told%20a%20forum%20on%20Monday%2C%20per%20the%20state%20news%20agency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.com%2Feconomy%2F1712447%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETASS%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdedollarization-russia-fraught-india-rupee-oil-trade-warning-us-dollar-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701165647000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65657d64c58b6f84123ad12d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdedollarization-russia-fraught-india-rupee-oil-trade-warning-us-dollar-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Moscow%20has%20encountered%20several%20complications%20since%20India%20insisted%20on%20paying%20for%20Russian%20oil%20in%20rupees%20rather%20than%20dollars.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22htan%40insider.com%20(Huileng%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdedollarization-russia-fraught-india-rupee-oil-trade-warning-us-dollar-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20COVID-19%20Enabled%20New%20Forms%20of%20Economic%20Abuse%20of%26nbsp%3BWomen%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F28141502%2Findia-6602002_1280.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20crisis%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20(UN)%20identified%20what%20it%20called%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unwomen.org%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fin-focus%2Fin-focus-gender-equality-in-covid-19-response%2Fviolence-against-women-during-covid-19%5C%22%3Eshadow%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20domestic%20violence%20against%20women.%20The%20UN%20includes%20in%20its%20definition%20of%20domestic%20violence%20what%20it%20refers%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldbank.org%2Fen%2Fwork-with-us%2Fhsd%2Fhome%2Fhsd_dapp_what_is_abuse%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20it%20explains%20as%3A%20%E2%80%9Cmaking%20or%20attempting%20to%20make%20a%20person%20financially%20dependent%20by%20maintaining%20total%20control%20over%20financial%20resources%2C%20withholding%20access%20to%20money%2C%20and%2For%20forbidding%20attendance%20at%20school%20or%20employment%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20have%20been%20researching%20economic%20violence%20in%20India%2C%20where%20it%20surged%20during%20periods%20of%20social%20distancing%20and%20lockdowns.%20This%20not%20only%20resulted%20in%20the%20reduction%20of%20safe%20spaces%20for%20women%20and%20girls%2C%20but%20also%20trapped%20them%20in%20a%20space%20where%20they%20were%20more%20easily%20economically%20exploited.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sps.ed.ac.uk%2Fnews-events%2Fevent%2Fspent-fighting-economic-abuse-india%5C%22%3Eresearch%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20COVID%20lockdowns%20spawned%20a%20whole%20new%20class%20of%20economic%20abuse%20of%20women%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEconomic%20abuse%20tends%20to%20involve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F1077801208315529%5C%22%3Econtrolling%20and%20coercive%20behaviour%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20partner%20and%20sometimes%20their%20in-laws%20or%20other%20family%20members%2C%20threatening%20her%20economic%20security%20and%20potential%20for%20self-sufficiency.%20While%20economic%20abuse%20can%20take%20many%20forms%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsurvivingeconomicabuse.org%2Fwhat-is-economic-abuse%2F%5C%22%3Ethree%20main%20types%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20sabotage%2C%20restriction%20and%20exploitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESabotage%20usually%20involves%20interfering%20in%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20money%20or%20in%20their%20work.%20Restriction%20is%20about%20controlling%20how%20women%20use%20money.%20And%20exploitation%20most%20often%20means%20a%20male%20partner%20or%20relative%20living%20off%20a%20woman%2C%20or%20insisting%20all%20debts%20go%20in%20her%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20previous%20research%20has%20revealed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2017-15493-001%5C%22%3Eunique%20forms%20of%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20embedded%20in%20specific%20sociocultural%20practices%20in%20India.%20For%20example%2C%20exploitation%20of%20%3Cem%3Estreedhan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(jewellery%20and%20movable%20or%20immovable%20assets%20given%20to%20a%20woman%20before%20and%20during%20her%20marriage)%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F370871643_Dowry_is_a_serious_economic_violence_Rethinking_Dowry_Law_in_India%5C%22%3Edowry%20practices%3C%2Fa%3E%20(money%20and%20gifts%20demanded%20by%20the%20groom%20and%20in-laws%20at%20the%20time%20of%20and%20after%20marriage)%20have%20been%20identified%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2017-15493-001%5C%22%3Ecommon%20form%20of%20economic%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20south%20Asian%20marriages.%20If%20a%20woman%20lives%20with%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20family%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Fchapter%2F10.1007%2F978-981-15-0653-6_3%5C%22%3Emay%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20her%20assets%20or%20income%20where%20multiple%20generations%20live%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomic%20abuse%20of%20women%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20our%20research%20in%20a%20city%20in%20Bihar%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20third-most%20populous%20state%20in%20the%20east%20of%20the%20country%2C%20we%20made%20a%2020-minute%20documentary%3A%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D-HvI1pUeuvI%5C%22%3ESpent%3A%20Fighting%20Economic%20Abuse%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20featuring%20five%20of%20the%2076%20women%20we%20spoke%20to.%20All%20but%20two%20were%20mothers%20with%20dependent%20children.%20We%20found%20that%20economic%20abuse%20was%20common%20irrespective%20of%20class%2C%20caste%2C%20religion%2C%20education%20or%20employment%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20woman%20we%20feature%2C%20Nitya%2C%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20allowed%20to%20work%20by%20her%20family.%20Instead%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20perform%20domestic%20chores%20around%20the%20clock.%20This%20typically%20included%20being%20required%20to%20cook%20seven%20or%20eight%20courses%20at%20dinner.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20her%20husband%20mocked%20her%20for%20not%20working.%20Nitya%20told%20us%20he%E2%80%99d%20say%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20don%E2%80%99t%20work%2C%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20point%20of%20your%20education%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20abusive%20husbands%20also%20refused%20to%20pay%20any%20household%20costs%20relating%20to%20women%20and%20children%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20girls.%20Another%20of%20our%20interviewees%2C%20Nilu%2C%20told%20us%20how%20her%20husband%20had%20refused%20to%20pay%20the%20medical%20bills%20relating%20to%20their%20daughter%E2%80%99s%20birth%20and%20tried%20to%20force%20her%20back%20to%20work%20with%20a%20month-old%20baby.%20She%20was%20forced%20to%20stay%20at%20her%20mother%E2%80%99s%20home%20to%20seek%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZubaida%E2%80%99s%20husband%20got%20angry%20whenever%20she%20asked%20for%20money%20for%20necessities%2C%20while%20spending%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20money%20on%20his%20own%20clothes%20and%20shoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20these%20women%20reported%20abuse%20that%20was%20embedded%20in%20cultural%20practices%2C%20such%20as%20demands%20for%20dowry.%20Nilu%20told%20us%20her%20husband%20pretended%20that%20he%20was%20not%20getting%20paid%20and%20made%20her%20father%20pay%20for%20everything%20in%20her%20house%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%20Her%20father%20agreed%20to%20ensure%20that%20Nilu%20was%20not%20thrown%20out%20of%20her%20marital%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20abusive%20tactics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20interviews%20suggested%20that%20abusive%20men%E2%80%99s%20bad%20treatment%20of%20their%20spouses%20tended%20to%20worsen%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20And%20the%20special%20circumstances%20associated%20with%20COVID%20restrictions%20enabled%20new%20forms%20of%20economic%20abuse%20of%20women%2C%20given%20the%20special%20circumstances%20associated%20with%20lockdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20gave%20abusive%20men%20new%20ways%20of%20controlling%20and%20abusing%20their%20wives%E2%80%99%20finances.%20In%20lockdown%20%E2%80%93%20and%20with%20the%20isolation%20that%20entailed%20%E2%80%93%20a%20family%E2%80%99s%20financial%20affairs%20became%20dependent%20on%20access%20to%20the%20internet%2C%20usually%20via%20shared%20mobile%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20women%20we%20talked%20to%2C%20Lakshmi%20%E2%80%93%20a%20high-ranking%20corporate%20employee%20%E2%80%93%20said%20she%20was%20duty-bound%20to%20keep%20her%20clients%E2%80%99%20details%20confidential.%20Lakshmi%20told%20us%20her%20husband%20took%20not%20only%20her%20social%20media%20and%20banking%20passwords%20but%20also%20managed%20to%20access%20her%20work%20WhatsApp%20account%2C%20used%20for%20communicating%20with%20teammates.%20He%20started%20impersonating%20her%20online%20and%20insulted%20her%20superior%2C%20which%20caused%20her%20serious%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20other%20women%20told%20us%20about%20their%20male%20relatives%20using%20their%20logins%20to%20clear%20out%20their%20bank%20accounts.%20Women%20also%20reported%20loans%20being%20taken%20out%20in%20their%20names%2C%20but%20having%20no%20access%20to%20money%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELockdown%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20prevent%20women%20from%20accessing%20their%20support%20groups%2C%20including%20their%20families.%20Nitya%20told%20us%20of%20being%20beaten%20by%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20allow%20her%20to%20speak%20to%20her%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProtection%20measures%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20law%20recognises%20economic%20abuse%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15436%2F1%2Fprotection_of_women_from_domestic_violence_act%252C_2005.pdf%5C%22%3EDomestic%20Violence%20Prevention%20Act%202005%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20includes%20deprivation%20of%20all%20economic%20and%20financial%20resources%20and%20restriction%20to%20shared%20household%20resources%20as%20well%20as%20exploitation%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20own%20belongings%2C%20such%20as%20their%20jewellery%20and%20other%20valuable%20possessions.%20But%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4350642%5C%22%3Eunderstanding%20of%20economic%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20its%20impact%20on%20women%20remains%20extremely%20low%20%E2%80%93%20both%20at%20government%20level%20and%20among%20professionals%20and%20service%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20serious%20problem.%20Economic%20abuse%20has%20a%20huge%20impact%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffbj.springeropen.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs43093-021-00074-9%5C%22%3Ephysical%20and%20mental%20wellbeing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20also%20been%20shown%20to%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Fchapter%2F10.1007%2F978-3-031-05640-6_7%5C%22%3Echildren%E2%80%99s%20health%20and%20wellbeing%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20economic%20abuse%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20urgent%20need%20to%20have%20open%20conversations%20about%20money%20in%20families%20and%20challenge%20ideas%20around%20masculinity%20and%20money.%20More%20importantly%2C%20policy%20makers%20and%20practitioners%20need%20to%20work%20together%20to%20address%20the%20role%20of%20the%20state%2C%20market%20and%20community%20institutions%20in%20facilitating%20economic%20abuse%20by%20reinforcing%20gender%20norms%2C%20including%20in%20financial%20transactions.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F212822%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPunita%20Chowbey%20is%20senior%20research%20fellow%2C%20Sheffield%20Hallam%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%2