f%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irishtimes.com%2Flife-style%2F2023%2F03%2F18%2Fsally-rooney-renters-are-being-exploited-and-evictions-must-be-stopped%2F%5C%22%3ESally%20Rooney%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irishtimes.com%2Fvideo%2Fvideo%2F2022%2F06%2F14%2Fdublin-has-become-blander-artists-protest-studio-closures%2F%5C%22%3Eclosure%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20arts%20spaces%20in%20Dublin%20given%20over%20to%20short-time%20lets%20is%20also%20a%20common%20cause%20for%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20nominated%20novels%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMurray%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Bee%20Sting%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20a%20tragicomedy%20of%20epic%20proportions.%20Clocking%20in%20at%20656%20pages%2C%20it%20follows%20the%20Barneses%20%E2%80%93%20mother%2C%20father%2C%2017-year-old%20daughter%20and%2012-year-old%20son%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%20places%20unbearable%20strain%20on%20an%20already%20tense%20family%20dynamic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FUMEbB0Jltn0%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%E2%80%99s%20slimmer%20offering%2C%20Prophet%20Song%2C%20takes%20place%20in%20a%20dystopian%20Ireland%20hurtling%20towards%20authoritarianism.%20It%20is%20both%20recognisable%20and%20unknown%20%E2%80%93%20Ireland%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9Cunder%20some%20foreign%20sky%E2%80%9D.%20Its%20main%20character%20is%20a%20stalwart%20of%20Irish%20literature%3A%20a%20mother%20and%20wife%20named%20Eilish.%20Her%20attempts%20to%20protect%20her%20family%20in%20a%20world%20not%20of%20her%20making%20is%20resonant%20back%20through%20the%20canon%2C%20while%20taking%20on%20a%20new%20and%20eerie%20prescience%20in%20Lynch%E2%80%99s%20portrait%20of%20an%20Irish%20police%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Bee%20Sting%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EProphet%20Song%3C%2Fem%3E%20deal%20with%20one%20of%20the%20abiding%20themes%20of%20Irish%20literature%20%E2%80%93%20the%20trickiness%20of%20memory%2C%20both%20personal%20and%20collective.%20This%20literary%20preoccupation%20with%20the%20past%20has%20sometimes%20come%20under%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202001%2C%20Irish%20Times%20journalist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irishtimes.com%2Fculture%2Fwriting-the-boom-1.273557%5C%22%3EFintan%20O%E2%80%99Toole%3C%2Fa%3E%20alleged%20that%20Irish%20writers%20were%20struggling%20to%20analyse%20the%20times%20in%20which%20they%20were%20living%2C%20instead%20reverting%20to%20old%20tropes%20and%20themes%20and%20depicting%20an%20Ireland%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20competent%20writers%20can%20do%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20with%20their%20eyes%20closed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Murray%20and%20Lynch%20seem%20to%20speak%20directly%20to%20O%E2%80%99Toole%E2%80%99s%20concern.%20In%20one%20instance%20in%20Prophet%20Song%2C%20Eilish%20muses%3A%20%E2%80%9CAll%20your%20life%20you%E2%80%99ve%20been%20asleep%2C%20all%20of%20us%20sleeping%20and%20now%20the%20great%20waking%20begins.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20both%20novels%20deal%20with%20wake-up%20calls.%20Murray%20revisits%20the%20financial%20crash%20%E2%80%93%20a%20moment%20in%20recent%20Irish%20history%20whose%20trauma%20remains%2C%20it%20could%20be%20argued%2C%20partially%20suppressed.%20Meanwhile%20Lynch%20takes%20aim%20at%20Irish%20political%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.maynoothuniversity.ie%2Fresearch%2Fspotlight-research%2Fare-far-right-threat-irish-democracy%5C%22%3Estability%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20complacency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F-Cx1IZEx_eE%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5C%5C%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Murray%E2%80%99s%20depictions%20of%20personal%2C%20buried%20histories%20and%20in%20Lynch%E2%80%99s%20concern%20with%20the%20vulnerability%20of%20consensus%20and%20humanity%2C%20these%20novels%20reflect%20how%20we%20can%20simultaneously%20know%20so%20much%20and%20so%20little%20of%20the%20people%20and%20places%20closest%20to%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20writers%20masterfully%20reveal%20the%20strangeness%20of%20familiarity%2C%20and%20the%20familiarity%20of%20strangeness.%20They%20both%20question%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20we%20know%20the%20depths%20of%20our%20own%20capabilities%2C%20for%20good%20and%20for%20bad%2C%20and%20sketch%20the%20intersection%20of%20existential%20crises%20with%20normal%2C%20individual%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWriting%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Stinging%20Fly%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstingingfly.org%2Freview%2Fthe-bee-sting%2F%5C%22%3EStephen%20Cox%3C%2Fa%3E%20wryly%20notes%20that%20Murray%E2%80%99s%20back%20catalogue%20could%20be%20summarised%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fbooks%2F2021%2Fsep%2F20%2Fwe-dont-know-ourselves-by-fintan-otoole-review-sweeping-account-of-irelands-evolutions%5C%22%3EWe%20Don%E2%80%99t%20Know%20Ourselves%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20%C3%A0%20la%20Fintan%20O%E2%80%99Toole%E2%80%99s%202021%20memoir%20of%20the%20same%20title.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20historically%20been%20the%20job%20of%20Irish%20writers%20to%20reflect%20the%20worst%20elements%20of%20their%20society%20back%20at%20itself.%20In%20%3Cem%3EProphet%20Song%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Bee%20Sting%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Lynch%20and%20Murray%20are%20continuing%20this%20tradition.%20Ireland%20should%20pay%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20has%20been%20updated%20to%20reflect%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20Booker%20prize.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOrlaith%20Darling%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20PhD%20candidate%2C%20Contemporary%20English%20Literatu