%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThree%20of%20the%20five%20accused%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fgujarat-dalit-man-forced-to-hold-former-employers-footwear-in-mouth-after-asking-for-salary%5C%22%3EMorbi%20Dalit%20incident%3C%2Fa%3E%20surrendered%20before%20the%20police%20on%20Monday%2C%20November%2028.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVibhuti%20Patel%2C%20a%20businesswoman%20from%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20Morbi%2C%20and%20her%20employers%20allegedly%20assaulted%20a%20Dalit%20man%2C%20threatened%20him%2C%20and%20even%20forced%20him%20to%20take%20her%20footwear%20in%20his%20mouth%20after%20he%20sought%20salary%20for%20the%20work%20he%20had%20done%20for%20her%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20Patel%20(27)%2C%20her%20brother%20Om%20Patel%20alias%20Om%20Sitapara%20(21)%2C%20and%20her%20business%20partner%20Raj%20Padshala%20(23)%20surrendered%20before%20Morbi%20deputy%20superintendent%20of%20police%20(SC-ST%20Cell)%20Pratipalsinh%20Zala%20early%20on%20Monday.%20The%20accused%20surrendered%20after%20their%20pleas%20seeking%20pre-arrest%20bail%20and%20the%20arrest%20of%20Mayur%20Karotara%20alias%20D.D.%20Rabari%2C%20another%20accused%20in%20the%20case%2C%20were%20rejected%20by%20a%20local%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20filed%20at%20A%20Division%20police%20station%20on%20November%2023%20noted%20that%20the%20accused%20allegedly%20assaulted%20Dalit%20man%2C%20Nilesh%20Dalsaniya%20(21)%2C%20his%20brother%20Mehul%2C%20and%20their%20neighbour%20Bhavesh%20Makwana%20at%20Raniba%20Industries%20Private%20Limited%20(RIPL)%20office%20on%20November%2022.%20Vibhuti%20Patel%20runs%20the%20company%2C%20which%20manufactures%20and%20exports%20ceramic%20tiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20alleged%20incident%20took%20place%20when%20Nilesh%20went%20to%20the%20office%20to%20demand%20his%20salary%20for%2016%20days%20of%20work%20he%20had%20done%20between%20October%202%20and%20October%2018.%20The%20FIR%20states%20that%20Vibhuti%20forced%20Nilesh%20to%20lie%20down%20before%20her%20and%20apologise%20to%20her%20by%20taking%20her%20footwear%20in%20his%20mouth.%20The%20accused%20also%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FIR%2C%20robbed%20Rs%20500%20and%20a%20smartwatch%20from%20Nilesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20FIR%2C%20the%20group%20dragged%20Dalsaniya%20to%20an%20elevator%2C%20took%20him%20to%20the%20terrace%20of%20the%20commercial%20building%2C%20and%20beat%20him%20up%20with%20a%20belt%20while%20also%20kicking%20and%20punching%20him%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fgujarat-dalit-man-forced-to-hold-former-employers-footwear-in-mouth-after-asking-for-salary%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EVibes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20five%20accused%20were%20booked%20as%20per%20Sections%20323%20(voluntarily%20causing%20hurt)%2C%20504%20(intentional%20insult%20with%20intent%20to%20provoke%20breach%20of%20the%20peace)%2C%20506(2)%20(criminal%20intimidation)%2C%20143%20(unlawful%20assembly)%2C%20147%20(rioting)%20and%20149%20(every%20member%20of%20unlawful%20assembly%20guilty%20of%20offence%20committed%20in%20prosecution%20of%20common%20object)%2C%20395%20(dacoity)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20and%20under%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(Prevention%20of%20Atrocities)%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20Parikshit%2C%20is%20at%20large.%20A%20day%20before%20their%20surrender%2C%20the%20accused%20had%20moved%20the%20court%20for%20anticipatory%20bail%20and%20protection%20from%20arrest%2C%20which%20was%20rejected.%20The%20court%20concurred%20with%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20submission%20that%20a%20%3Cem%3Eprima%20facie%3C%2Fem%3E%20case%20is%20made%20out%20against%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701160228000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F02154556%2FDalit-Lives-Matter-PTI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Faccused-in-the-morbi-dalit-assault-case-surrender-to-police-local-court-rejects-bail-pleas%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20businesswoman%20from%20Gujarat's%20Morbi%20and%20her%20employers%20allegedly%20assaulted%20a%20Dalit%20man%2C%20threatened%20him%2C%20and%20even%20forced%20him%20to%20take%20her%20footwear%20in%20his%20mouth%20after%20he%20sought%20salary%20for%20the%20work%20he%20had%20done%20for%20her%20company.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Faccused-in-the-morbi-dalit-assault-case-surrender-to-police-local-court-rejects-bail-pleas%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Alia%20is%20slaying%20her%20short%20hairdo%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701160200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105549829%2Cimgsize-46412.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Falia-bhatt-is-slaying-her-short-hairdo-heres-proof%2Fphotostory%2F105549829.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105549829.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%E2%80%8BAlia%20Bhatt%20is%20slaying%20her%20short%20hairdo%20-%20here's%20proof%E2%80%8B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Falia-bhatt-is-slaying-her-short-hairdo-heres-proof%2Fphotostory%2F105549829.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Opinion%3A%20A%20Survey%20Of%20200%20Indian%20NGOs%20And%2010%20Big%20Takeaways%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E'Feeding%20America'%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20charities%20in%20the%20US%2C%20raised%20over%20%24%204%20billion%20in%202022.%20India's%20largest%20similar%20organisation%20supplying%20meals%20raised%20about%20%24%200.07%20billion.%20Keeping%20aside%20the%20comparison%20with%20a%20much%20larger%20economy%20and%20charity%2C%20consider%20the%20size%20of%20the%20need%20in%20India.%20There%20is%20so%20much%20more%20that%20non-profits%20can%20achieve%2C%20and%20help%20accelerate%20India's%20progress%20towards%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%202030%20agenda%20-%20if%20they%20are%20enabled%20to%20grow%20and%20achieve%20their%20potential%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20holding%20back%20Indian%20non-profits%3F%20We%20have%20several%20million%20of%20them%20-%20NITI%20Aayog's%20Darpan%20portal%20shows%20over%201.75%20lakh%20registered%20NGOs%2C%20and%20estimates%20elsewhere%20range%20up%20to%203%20million.%20They%20come%20in%20myriad%20avatars%20-%20societies%2C%20trusts%2C%20Section%208%20companies%20and%20more%2C%20governed%20by%20different%20laws%20at%20the%20Centre%20and%20state%20levels.%20There%20is%20no%20single%20government%20agency%20or%20regulator%20that%20governs%20them%20all%2C%20and%20monitors%20the%20health%20of%20the%20sector.%20We%20sorely%20lack%20credible%20and%20updated%20data%20on%20the%20size%2C%20funding%20patterns%2C%20sectoral%20trends%2C%20growth%20or%20anything%20else%20that%20can%20aid%20thoughtful%20decision%20making%20from%20philanthropy%20or%20policy%20makers%20for%20helping%20the%20sector%20work%20at%20its%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20addressing%20this%20glaring%20gap%2C%20we%20tried%20to%20map%20the%20top%20200%20non-profits%20in%20India%20by%20their%20annual%20budget%2C%20the%20only%20objective%20and%20verified%20(signed%20by%20the%20auditors)%20parameter%20we%20have%20publicly%20available%20(through%20the%20annual%20reports)%20to%20assess%20the%20size%20of%20the%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20looked%20at%20a%20particular%20type%20of%20non-profit%20-%20an%20independent%20non-profit%20with%20its%20own%20mission%20statement%2C%20with%20at%20least%20a%20part%20of%20its%20work%20in%20implementation%2C%20raising%20money%20from%20multiple%20types%20of%20funders%20without%20being%20predominantly%20funded%20by%20a%20single%20donor.%20This%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20an%20impact-oriented%20non-profit%20you%20and%20I%20donate%20to%2C%20or%20the%20CSR%20teams%20engage%20with.%20This%20boundary%20excludes%20most%20corporate%20CSR%20foundations%2C%20philanthropic%2FHNI%2Ffamily%20foundations%20that%20are%20primarily%20funding%20agencies%2C%20multi-lateral%20institutions%2C%20and%20large%20educational%20institutions%20and%20hospitals%20that%20generate%20significant%20revenue%20through%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20important%20takeaways%20from%20survey%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETop%20200%20non-profits%20in%20India%20are%20in%20the%20annual%20budget%20range%20of%20Rs%2010%20crore%20to%20800%20crore.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAnnually%2C%20they%20secure%20about%20Rs%208%2C000-9%2C000%20crore%20in%20funding%20(about%20USD%201%20Billion).%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20source%20of%20this%20capital%20annually%20is%20split%20almost%20equally%20between%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20funding.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20three%20years%20we%20looked%20at%20-%202019-2022%20-%20the%20total%20pool%20of%20capital%20to%20this%20cohort%20did%20not%20change%20significantly%20when%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%20and%20a%20Covid-related%20spike.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChildren%2C%20community%20development%2C%20education%2C%20healthcare%20and%20livelihood%20are%20the%20top%20sectors%20these%20organisations%20work%20in.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAbout%2018%25%20of%20the%20organisations%20have%20global%20origin%2F%20affiliation%2C%20and%20they%20received%2030%25%20of%20the%20total%20funding.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAt%20an%20aggregate%20level%2C%20the%20non-profits%20have%20a%20year-end%20income%20surplus%20ranging%20from%204%25%20to%207%25%20of%20the%20total%20money%20raised%20each%20year.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFinances%20are%20volatile.%20Almost%2020%25%20saw%20an%20income%20change%20of%20over%2050%25%20in%202021-22.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHeadquarters%20of%20these%20large%20NGOs%20are%20clustered%20around%20the%20hubs%20of%20corporate%20and%20commercial%20activity%20in%20India.%20Underdeveloped%20areas%20would%20benefit%20from%20the%20presence%20of%20locally%20headquartered%20non-profits%20capable%20of%20raising%20and%20deploying%20large%20grants%20for%20local%20development.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMost%20organisations%20that%20are%20large%20today%2C%20started%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades.%20Several%20factors%20play%20a%20role%20in%20the%20success%20of%20relatively%20younger%20non-profits%20-%20the%20influx%20of%20professional%20talent%2C%20new%20philanthropists%20with%20a%20different%20vision%2C%20changing%20regulatory%20environment%2C%20and%20most%20importantly%20the%20evolving%20nature%20of%20societal%20problems%20with%20the%20economic%20and%20technological%20progress%20India%20has%20made.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20these%20200%2C%20there%20are%20thousands%20of%20organisations%20doing%20good%20work%20but%20unfortunately%20not%20of%20significant%20size.%20Their%20localised%20impact%20still%20matters%2C%20but%20meaningful%20scale%20is%20not%20always%20possible%20at%20their%20suboptimal%20size.%20Growth%20alone%20need%20not%20be%20the%20focus%20for%20every%20organisation%2C%20but%20there's%20much%20headroom%20for%20the%20ones%20with%20demonstrated%20models%20of%20impact%20that%20can%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20can%20help%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20regulatory%20and%20policy%20overhaul%20to%20foster%20non-profits%20of%20all%20sizes%20through%20nuanced%20measures%2C%20conscious%20focus%20on%20organisation%20building%20with%20support%20from%20philanthropists%20through%20non-programmatic%20grants%20and%20capacity%20strengthening%2C%20and%20a%20concerted%20effort%20on%20building%20trust%20through%20transparency%20are%20some%20measures%20that%20need%20urgent%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20India's%20largest%20private%20sector%20company%20spends%20as%20much%20on%20social%20impact%20through%20CSR%20(Corporate%20Social%20Responsibility)%20single-handedly%2C%20as%20does%20the%20largest%20non-profit%20in%20India%20funded%20by%20multiple%20donors.%20Less%20than%20half%20of%20corporate%20India's%20sizeable%20pool%20of%20mandatory%20CSR%20spend%20of%20Rs%2025%2C000%20crore%20annually%20goes%20to%20independent%20non-profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20achieve%20sustainable%20and%20inclusive%20growth%20as%20envisioned%20in%20SDG%202030%2C%20it%20is%20important%20that%20the%20impact%20focused%20non-profits%20grow%20along%20with%20the%20Indian%20economy%20and%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Vrunda%20Bansode%20is%20passionate%20about%20making%20actionable%20data%20available%20for%20decision%20making%20in%20the%20social%20sector%2C%20and%20has%20worked%20on%20multiple%20pioneering%20data%20products%20at%20Sattva%20Consulting%2C%20a%20leading%20impact%20consulting%20firm.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701159780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-03%2Fu6sqpbpg_hunger-helpline_625x300_26_March_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-survey-of-200-indian-ngos-and-10-big-takeaways-4613160%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Feeding%20America'%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20charities%20in%20the%20US%2C%20raised%20over%20%24%204%20billion%20in%202022.%20India's%20largest%20similar%20organisation%20supplying%20meals%20raised%20about%20%24%200.07%20billion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-survey-of-200-indian-ngos-and-10-big-takeaways-4613160%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-survey-of-200-indian-ngos-and-10-big-takeaways-4613160%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-survey-of-200-indian-ngos-and-10-big-takeaways-4613160%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20Parliamentary%20Panel%E2%80%99s%20Rubber%20Stamp%2C%20Path%20Clear%20for%20New%20Criminal%20Code%20and%20%E2%80%98Police%20Raj'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F16195602%2FScreen-Shot-2021-08-16-at-7.55.39-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20August%2011%2C%202023%20the%20Union%20government%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20a%20proposed%20new%20criminal%20code%20for%20India%20consisting%20of%20three%20Bills%20that%20would%20respectively%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%20with%20the%20proposed%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBNS-IPC%E2%80%9D)%2C%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C%201973%20with%20the%20proposed%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBNSS-CrPC%E2%80%9D)%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%20with%20the%20proposed%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBSA-IEA%E2%80%9D).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EQuantitatively%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20changes%20made%20by%20the%20three%20Bills%20to%20the%20existing%20criminal%20code%20are%20limited%20%E2%80%93%20they%20leave%20untouched%20some%2070-75%25%20of%20the%20current%20law.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-three-criminal-law-bills-using-criminal-law-to-establish-permanent-extra-constitutional-emergency-powers%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0that%20although%20quantitatively%20limited%2C%20some%20of%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Echanges%20sought%20to%20be%20made%20by%20the%20Bills%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Equalitatively%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Egame-changing.%20They%20would%20equip%20the%20government%20with%20adequate%20power%20to%20hollow%20out%20our%20democracy%20and%20transform%20India%20into%20a%20fascist%20state%20%E2%80%93%20should%20the%20government%20choose%20to%20deploy%20the%20new%20laws%20to%20their%20fullest%20extent.%20The%20proposed%20new%20laws%20would%20enable%20the%20government%20to%20dramatically%20scale%20up%20arrest%2C%20detention%2C%20prosecution%20and%20imprisonment%20of%20law%20abiding%20democratic%20opponents%2C%20dissidents%20and%20activists.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20identified%20in%20this%20regard%20a%20dozen%20chilling%20features%20of%20the%20new%20Criminal%20Code%20as%20requiring%20special%20attention%3A%20(1)%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20legitimate%2C%20lawful%2C%20non-violent%20democratic%20speech%20or%20action%20as%20%E2%80%98terrorism%E2%80%99%3B%20(2)%20the%20broadening%20of%20the%20offence%20of%20sedition%C2%A0%20in%20a%20new%20and%20more%20vicious%20avatar%20(as%20what%20I%20would%20call%20%E2%80%9Csedition-plus%E2%80%9D)%3B%20(3)%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20potential%20for%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20prosecution%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20targeted%2C%20politically-biased%20prosecution%20of%20ideological%20and%20political%20opponents%3B%20(4)%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20a%20common%20mode%20of%20political%20protest%20against%20government%20through%20fasting%3B%20(5)%20encouraging%20the%20use%20of%20force%20against%20any%20assembly%20of%20persons%3B%20(6)%20exponentially%20enhancing%20%E2%80%98police%20raj%E2%80%99%20by%20criminalising%20%E2%80%9Cresisting%2C%20refusing%2C%20ignoring%20or%20disregarding%20to%20conform%20to%20any%20direction%20given%20by%20%5Ba%20police%20officer%5D%20(sic)%E2%80%9D%20on%20pain%20of%20immediate%20detention%20by%20the%20police%20officer%3B%20(7)%20enhancing%20handcuffing%3B%20(8)%20maximising%20police%20custody%20during%20investigation%3B%20(9)%20making%20the%20recording%20of%20a%20FIR%20discretionary%20for%20the%20police%3B%20(10)%20dialling%20up%20the%20pain%20of%20imprisonment%3B%20(11)%20compelling%20all%20persons%20(even%20those%20not%20accused%20of%20any%20crime)%20to%20provide%20their%20biometrics%20to%20the%20government%3B%20and%20(12)%20shielding%20of%20some%20of%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20activities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fknow-the-three-new-criminal-bills-whats-new-and-whats-old%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Union%2520home%2520minister%252C%2520Amit%2Cto%2520escape%2520%25E2%2580%259Ccolonial%2520legacy%25E2%2580%259D.%5C%22%3EKnow%20The%20Three%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%3A%20What%E2%80%99s%20New%20and%20What%E2%80%99s%20Old%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommittee%E2%80%99s%20report%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20three%20Bills%20were%20promptly%20referred%20by%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20the%20department-related%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%20for%20review.%20On%20November%2010%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Committee%2C%20which%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20ruling%20coalition%2C%20submitted%20to%20parliament%20its%20reports%20on%20the%20three%20Bills.%20As%20expected%2C%20the%20reports%20hail%2C%20endorse%20and%20rubber-stamp%20the%20Bills.%20The%20Committee%20addresses%20only%20a%20small%20proportion%20of%20the%20three%20Bills%3A%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20the%20356%20clauses%20of%20BNS-IPC%3B%20around%205%25%20of%20the%20533%20clauses%20of%20BNSS-CrPC%3B%20and%20around%206%25%20of%20the%20170%20clauses%20of%20BSA-IEA.%20The%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20mostly%20deal%20with%20inconsequential%20drafting%20and%20editorial%20errors.%20The%20central%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Bills%20on%20democracy%20%E2%80%94%20is%20not%20addressed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20few%20substantive%20recommendations%20made%20by%20the%20Committee%20do%20not%20hamper%20the%20core%20objective%20of%20the%20Bills%2C%20which%20is%20to%20establish%20draconian%20police%20raj%20in%20the%20country.%20They%20include%3A%20(i)%20make%20adultery%20gender-neutral%20and%20maintain%20adultery%20as%20a%20crime%20given%20the%20sanctity%20of%20marriage%20in%20the%20Indian%20tradition%3B%20(ii)%20do%20not%20delete%20Section%20current%20153AA%20of%20IPC%20which%20bans%20processions%20in%20which%20arms%20are%20carried%3B%20(iii)%20add%20acts%20against%20sovereignty%20of%20India%20to%20the%20list%20of%20acts%20of%20terrorism%3B%20(iv)%20clarify%20that%20the%20offence%20of%20grievous%20hurt%20by%20a%20mob%20would%20cover%20acts%20on%20grounds%20of%20religion%20and%20community%20of%20the%20victims%3A%20(v)%20criminalise%20attacks%20against%20healthcare%20workers%3B%20(vi)%20reduce%20punishment%20for%20use%20of%20force%20against%20public%20servants%3B%20(vii)%20exclude%20economic%20offenders%20from%20expanded%20handcuffing%20under%20the%20new%20laws%3B%20(viii)%20limit%20the%20time%20period%20within%20which%20a%20person%20may%20be%20prosecuted%20for%20the%20new%20crime%20of%20refusing%20to%20obey%20directions%20of%20the%20police%3B%20(ix)%20clarify%20the%20maximum%20limit%20for%20police%20custody%20during%20investigation%3B%20(x)%20require%20that%20reasons%20be%20provided%20for%20the%20executive%20branch%20commuting%20sentences%3B%20(xi)%20put%20safeguards%20against%20risk%20of%20misuse%20of%20digital%20evidence%3B%20(xii)%20clarify%20some%20key%20definitions%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Clife%20imprisonment%E2%80%9D%3B%20%E2%80%9Ccommunity%20service%E2%80%9D%3B%20%E2%80%9Corganised%20crime%E2%80%9D%3B%20%E2%80%9Cpetty%20organised%20crime%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%20%E2%80%9Cintimidation%E2%80%9D%20(part%20of%20the%20new%20definition%20of%20a%20terrorist%20act)%3B%20and%20(xiii)%20do%20not%20substitute%20the%20reference%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20unsoundness%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20defence%20by%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20illness%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20will%20widen%20the%20scope%20of%20defence%20against%20criminal%20prosecution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Committee%20report%20acknowledges%20that%20although%20the%20current%20crime%20of%20sedition%20will%20be%20deleted%20in%20the%20new%20code%2C%20%E2%80%9Cprovisions%20of%20sedition%20law%20that%20are%20suggested%20for%20removal%20are%20somehow%20retained%20in%20clause%20150%20(of%20BNS-IPC)%20in%20mild%20form%20addressing%20actions%20that%20jeopardise%20the%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%20That%20consultations%20held%20by%20the%20Committee%20during%20its%20review%20were%20largely%20with%20%E2%80%9Cfriendly%E2%80%9D%20sources%20is%20indicated%20by%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20Committee%20that%20during%20its%20hearings%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3Eall%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Edomain%20experts%20welcomed%20the%20initiative%20of%20the%20Government%20to%20introduce%20these%20legislations%20in%20Parliament%E2%80%9D%20(emphasis%20supplied%2C%20page%2011%20of%20the%20Report%20on%20BNS-IPC).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOpposition%E2%80%99s%20dissent%20inadequate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20dissenting%20notes%20of%20the%20opposition%20members%20of%20the%20Committee%20are%20annexed%20to%20the%20Reports.%20The%20opposition%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20have%20utterly%20failed%20to%20put%20together%20a%20cogent%20and%20effective%20argument%20against%20the%20draconian%20Bills.%20Many%20of%20them%20have%20simply%20signed%20onto%20pre-prepared%20photocopies%20of%20comments%20without%20any%20evidence%20of%20independent%20application%20of%20minds.%20Their%20comments%20miss%20the%20forest%20for%20the%20trees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20main%20points%20made%20by%20the%20opposition%20in%20their%20notes%20of%20dissent%20include%3A%20(1)%20the%20claims%20of%20the%20government%20on%20the%20aims%2C%20objects%2C%20rationale%20and%20benefits%20of%20the%20Bill%20are%20false%3B%20(2)%20public%20consultation%20on%20the%20Bills%20is%20grossly%20inadequate%20and%20he%20Bills%20are%20being%20processed%20with%20undue%20hurry%3B%20(3)%20the%20Bills%20should%20have%20English%20names%3B%20(4)%20the%20Bills%20enhance%20the%20police%20powers%20of%20the%20Union%20without%20adequate%20checks%20and%20balances%3B%20(5)%20marital%20rape%20has%20not%20been%20criminalised%3B%20(6)%20handcuffing%20is%20being%20expanded%3B%20(7)%20the%20Bills%20provide%20for%20excess%20police%20custody%20during%20investigation%3B%20(8)%20safeguards%20are%20required%20for%20use%20of%20electronic%20evidence%3B%20and%20for%20the%20proposed%20provisions%20on%20trials%20in%20absentia%3B%20(9)%20issues%20such%20as%20terrorism%20and%20organised%20crime%20should%20be%20kept%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20special%20laws%20with%20special%20procedural%20safeguards%3B%20the%20proposed%20provisions%20on%20terrorism%20overlap%20with%20UAPA%20provisions%20on%20terrorism%20and%20are%20over-broad%3B%20consent%20of%20states%20which%20have%20existing%20state%20legislation%20on%20organised%20crime%20must%20be%20consulted%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bills%20on%20organised%20crime%3B%20(10)%20vesting%20of%20power%20of%20commutation%20of%20sentences%20in%20the%20executive%20violates%20separation%20of%20powers%3B%20(11)%20proposed%20several%20proposed%20punishments%20are%20either%20too%20low%20or%20too%20high%3B%20and%20(12)%20some%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bills%20are%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20dissent%20fails%20to%20adequately%20and%20squarely%20raise%20the%20larger%20issue%20of%20the%20illiberal%20and%20anti-democratic%20character%20of%20the%20Bills.%20Indeed%2C%20this%20may%20be%20because%20some%20of%20them%2C%20such%20as%20P.%20Chidambaram%2C%20are%20themselves%20architects%20of%20notorious%20draconian%20laws%20in%20the%20past%20and%20can%20have%20little%20ideological%20objection%20to%20a%20police%20raj.%20It%20does%20not%20seem%20that%20the%20opposition%20political%20parties%20have%20any%20serious%20intention%20to%20oppose%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20draconian%20new%20criminal%20code%20%E2%80%93%20which%20some%20of%20them%20may%20be%20looking%20forward%20to%20using%20against%20their%20own%20opponents%20when%20they%20come%20to%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F28132349%2F331609082_635812508553983_5561016377366099008_n.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F28132349%2F331609082_635812508553983_5561016377366099008_n.jpg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F28132349%2F331609082_635812508553983_5561016377366099008_n-300x157.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686716%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22522%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EP.%20Chidambaram.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FPChidambaram.INC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20way%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20Bills%20have%20now%20been%20endorsed%20by%20the%C2%A0%20Standing%20Committee%20with%20relatively%20minor%20suggestions%2C%20it%20appears%20quite%20certain%20now%20that%20they%20will%20be%20adopted%20by%20parliament%20and%20enacted%20as%20laws%20in%20short%20order%20without%20any%20change%20in%20their%20fundamental%20anti-democratic%20character.%20When%20that%20happens%2C%20although%20we%20may%20not%20immediately%20recognise%20it%2C%20we%20will%20cease%20in%20effect%20to%20be%20a%20functioning%20democracy%20in%20any%20meaningful%20way.%20What%20is%20the%20way%20forward%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFirst%2C%20we%20must%20raise%20public%20awareness%20of%20the%20extremely%20dangerous%2C%20anti-national%20role%20of%20criminal%20law%20as%20a%20weapon%20against%20democracy%20through%20criminalising%20of%20dissent%20and%20of%20democratic%20action%20in%20the%20name%20of%20vague%20and%20ill-defined%20crimes%20such%20as%20terrorism%2C%20sedition%2C%20attacks%20against%20the%20unity%2C%20sovereignty%2C%20integrity%20of%20India%20as%20well%20as%20by%20vesting%20discretionary%20power%20in%20the%20police%20which%20is%20not%20tightly%20controlled%20by%20civilain%20authority%20and%20ultimately%20by%20an%20independent%20judiciary.%20These%20laws%20have%20for%20years%20been%20misused%20for%20targeted%2C%20biased%20persecution%20of%20democratic%20dissent%20and%20activism%20for%20decades%20through%20selective%20prosecution.%20All%20this%20is%20likely%20now%20to%20increase%20substantially%20under%20the%20expanded%20power%20being%20given%20to%20the%20State%20to%20suppress%20democracy%20using%20criminal%20law.%20We%20must%20demand%20reform%20of%20all%20such%20criminal%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecond%2C%20we%20must%20recognise%20honestly%20where%20we%20stand%20today.%20It%20is%20undeniable%20that%20our%20current%20criminal%20justice%20system%20is%20indeed%20colonial%20and%20authoritarian.%20It%20is%20designed%20to%20protect%20power%2C%20not%20to%20protect%20democracy%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20power.%20The%20Congress%2C%20which%20ruled%20India%20for%20three%20unbroken%20decades%20from%20from%201947%20to%201977%2C%20made%20several%20amendments%20and%20reforms.%20But%20it%20not%20only%20failed%20to%20scrap%20the%20colonial%20criminal%20justice%20system%20lock%2C%20stock%20and%20barrel%20and%20build%20a%20new%20democratic%20criminal%20justice%20system%20consistent%20with%20the%20preambular%20values%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20it%20actually%20made%20criminal%20justice%20even%20more%20draconian%20than%20it%20was%20under%20the%20British.%20The%20result%20is%20that%20we%20today%20have%20a%20dystopic%20criminal%20justice%20system%20which%20has%20become%20an%20engine%20of%20oppression%20of%20common%20people%20and%20suppression%20of%20democracy.%20There%20is%20therefore%20undeniably%20a%20genuine%20need%20to%20discard%20the%20current%20criminal%20justice%20system%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20a%20new%20one.%20Fascist%20forces%20have%20taken%20advantage%20of%20this%20demand%20to%20put%20in%20place%20even%20more%20draconian%20and%20repressive%20powers%20while%20pretending%20that%20they%20are%20meeting%20the%20demand%20to%20overthrow%20the%20hated%20colonial%20system%20and%20are%20replacing%20it%20with%20a%20just%20and%20democratic%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThird%2C%20there%20is%20no%20long%20term%20option%20except%20a%20long%20and%20substantive%20democratic%20struggle%20against%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20police%20state%20in%20India%20for%20our%20liberty.%20We%20must%20use%20the%20upcoming%20parliamentary%20debates%20on%20the%20new%20criminal%20code%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20enactment%20and%20implementation%2C%20as%20the%20basis%20for%20a%20democratic%20mass%20movement%20demanding%20a%20new%20post-colonial%2C%20post-feudal%2C%20democratic%2C%20humane%20and%20just%20system%20of%20criminal%20law%20in%20India%2C%20consistent%20with%20global%20human%20rights%20norms%20and%20best%20practice.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20criminal%20law%20is%20historically%20heavily%20tilted%20towards%20criminalising%20acts%20against%20the%20state%20and%20against%20property%20rights%20(roughly%2080%25%20of%20our%20criminal%20laws)%20rather%20than%20criminalising%20acts%20against%20individuals%20(only%20roughly%2015%25%20of%20our%20criminal%20laws).%20In%20contrast%2C%20some%2040%25%20of%20laws%20in%20Norway%20criminalise%20crimes%20against%20individuals%20(as%20against%2060%25%20of%20Norwegian%20criminal%20law%20criminalising%20acts%20against%20the%20state%20or%20property).%20This%20needs%20correction.%20Like%20in%20several%20other%20countries%2C%20our%20criminal%20code%20must%20include%20provisions%20against%20genocide%2C%20crimes%20against%20humanity%2C%20crimes%20during%20armed%20conflict%2C%20torture%2C%20crimes%20against%20civil%20rights%2C%20violation%20of%20constitutional%20values%2C%20hate%20speech%2C%20caste%20or%20religious%20discrimination%20against%20a%20marginalised%20group.%20We%20have%20no%20time%20to%20lose.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EG.%20Mohan%20Gopal%20is%20an%20advocate%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20and%20a%20renowned%20legal%20academician.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701159324000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F16195602%2FScreen-Shot-2021-08-16-at-7.55.39-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-rubber-stamp-new-criminal-code-police-raj%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20few%20substantive%20recommendations%20made%20by%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%20do%20not%20hamper%20the%20core%20objective%20of%20the%20Bills%20and%20the%20impact%20they%20will%20have%20on%20democracy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-rubber-stamp-new-criminal-code-police-raj%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Right%20Wing%20Is%20on%20the%20Rise%20Globally%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2F12204307%2Funnamed.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%20Calling%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0How%20does%20India%20look%20from%20afar%3F%20Looming%20world%20power%20or%20dysfunctional%20democracy%3F%20And%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20Britain%2C%20and%20the%20West%2C%20that%20India%20needs%20to%20know%20about%20and%20perhaps%20learn%20from%3F%20This%20fortnightly%20column%20helps%20forge%20the%20connections%20so%20essential%20in%20our%20globalising%20world.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98The%20genie%20is%20out%20of%20the%20bottle%E2%80%99.%20So%20declared%20Dutch%20politician%20Geert%20Wilders%20last%20week%20after%20the%20surprise%20election%20victory%20of%20his%20hard%20right%20anti-immigrant%20party%20in%20the%20Netherlands.%20For%20decades%20he%E2%80%99s%20been%20shunned%20and%20reviled.%20Now%20this%20flamboyant%20politician%20with%20bouffant%20blond%20hair%20and%20a%20spectacular%20comb%20over%20(remind%20you%20of%20anyone%3F)%20will%20lead%20the%20biggest%20single%20party%20in%20the%20Dutch%20parliament.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20331px)%2085vw%2C%20331px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22331%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed.jpg%20526w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed-247x300.jpg%20247w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-649461%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22402%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Netherlands%20is%20not%20a%20touchstone%20for%20global%20political%20trends.%20But%20it%20is%20by%20most%20standards%20a%20strong%20and%20stable%20democracy%20which%20avoids%20political%20extremism%20of%20right%20or%20left.%20When%20the%20populist%20right%20makes%20inroads%20here%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20needs%20to%20sit%20up%20and%20take%20notice.%20And%20in%20the%20same%20week%2C%20another%20right-wing%20populist%20(with%20another%20dubious%20hair%20style)%2C%20Javier%20Milei%2C%20also%20achieved%20an%20against-the-odds%20election%20victory%20to%20become%20the%20new%20president%20of%20Argentina%2C%20one%20of%20Latin%20America%E2%80%99s%20larger%20nations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20not%20a%20uniform%20global%20trend%2C%20of%20course.%20The%20centre%20left%20is%20in%20power%20(for%20now)%20in%20two%20of%20the%20west%E2%80%99s%20major%20democracies%2C%20Germany%20and%20the%20United%20States%3B%20in%20Brazil%2C%20the%20leftist%20Lula%20da%20Silva%20succeeded%20in%20evicting%20the%20hard%20right%20Jair%20Bolsonaro%20last%20year%3B%20and%20in%20Britain%2C%20the%20social%20democratic%20Labour%20Party%20is%20likely%20to%20return%20to%20power%20next%20year%20after%2014%20years%20in%20opposition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20across%20much%20of%20the%20world%2C%20voters%20are%20turning%20to%20populists%20who%20are%20intensely%20distrustful%20of%20the%20institutions%20on%20which%20liberal%20democracy%20is%20built%3A%20fair%20and%20unfettered%20elections%3B%20an%20unrestricted%20media%3B%20religious%20tolerance%3B%20and%20political%20pluralism.%20At%20times%2C%20this%20feels%20like%20a%20rerun%20of%20the%20early%201930s.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWilders%20is%20not%20likely%20to%20emerge%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Dutch%20elections%20as%20his%20country%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister.%20His%20party%20will%20have%2037%20seats%20in%20the%20150-seat%20parliament%20%E2%80%93%20the%20largest%20party%20but%20a%20long%20way%20short%20of%20a%20majority.%20The%20initial%20signs%20are%20that%20centre%20right%20parties%20will%20refuse%20to%20enter%20a%20coalition%20with%20Wilders%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20one%20shoudn%E2%80%99t%20deal%20with%20the%20devil.%20That%20will%20allow%20Wilders%20to%20moan%20that%20the%20political%20establishment%20has%20closed%20ranks%20to%20keep%20him%20out%20of%20power%20%E2%80%93%20which%20of%20course%20will%20incense%20his%20hard-line%20supporters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwhat-explains-the-political-rights-ascendancy-to-global-power%5C%22%3EWhat%20Explains%20the%20Political%20Right%E2%80%99s%20Ascendancy%20to%20Global%20Power%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20Wilders%E2%80%99%20policies%20are%20not%20simply%20right%20of%20centre%3B%20they%20are%2C%20by%20any%20standards%2C%20extremist.%20His%20party%20stands%20for%20cutting%20net%20immigration%20to%20the%20Netherlands%20to%20zero%20and%20banning%20mosques%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3EQuran%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20has%20a%20conviction%20for%20inciting%20hatred.%20There%20is%20a%20rank%20odour%20of%20Islamophobia%20and%20intolerance%20about%20him%20and%20his%20party.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELook%20across%20Europe%2C%20and%20the%20populist%20right%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%20Italy%E2%80%99s%20Prime%20Minister%20Georgia%20Melon%20began%20her%20political%20career%20in%20movements%20which%20sought%20to%20resurrect%20Italian%20fascism%2C%20and%20her%20current%20party%2C%20the%20Brothers%20of%20Italy%2C%20is%20regarded%20as%20the%20most%20right-wing%20to%20govern%20the%20country%20since%20the%20collapse%20of%20Mussolini%E2%80%99s%20dictatorship%2080%20years%20ago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20have%20been%20pockets%20of%20hard%20right%20influence%20in%20Eastern%20Europe%20for%20a%20while%20%E2%80%93%20notably%20in%20Hungary%20and%20Poland%20%E2%80%93%20where%20arguably%20democratic%20traditions%20and%20institutions%20are%20not%20as%20strongly%20embedded%20because%20of%20the%20decades%20of%20Soviet%20domination.%20In%20France%2C%20the%20hard%20right%20Marine%20Le%20Pen%20has%20been%20runner-up%20in%20the%20last%20two%20presidential%20elections.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20the%20right%E2%80%99s%20shadow%20is%20getting%20bigger.%20In%20Germany%2C%20the%20AfD%20(Alternative%20for%20Germany)%20has%20more%20than%2070%20seats%20in%20the%20national%20parliament%20and%20is%20a%20serious%20electoral%20contender.%20In%20Scandinavia%20too%20%E2%80%93%20a%20model%20of%20political%20moderation%20for%20many%20decades%20%E2%80%93%20the%20right%20is%20on%20the%20rise%20with%20right-wing%20populists%20being%20the%20second%20biggest%20party%20in%20the%20national%20parliaments%20of%20Sweden%20and%20Finland.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20movements%20are%20not%20a%20cohesive%20political%20group%3A%20some%20are%20principally%20nationalist%3B%20others%20racist%20or%20reactionary%3B%20others%20again%20are%20Eurosceptics%2C%20wanting%20to%20build%20on%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20example%20%E2%80%93%20in%20part%20shaped%20by%20the%20populist%20right%20%E2%80%93%20and%20withdraw%20from%20the%20European%20Union.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3EThe%20Political%20Ethics%20of%20the%20Indian%20Political%20Right%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20root%20cause%20is%20the%20unease%20of%20those%20who%20feel%20they%20will%20lose%20out%20on%20jobs%20and%20housing%20because%20of%20large-scale%20immigration%2C%20exacerbated%20by%20economic%20stagnation%20and%20an%20unsettling%20level%20of%20global%20turbulence.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMilei%E2%80%99s%20victory%20in%20Argentina%20is%20a%20reminder%20that%20populism%20continues%20to%20pack%20a%20political%20punch%20in%20Latin%20America%20after%20the%20eclipse%20of%20Bolsonaro.%20Argentina%20has%20something%20of%20a%20tradition%20of%20maverick%20political%20leaders%20%E2%80%93%20after%20all%2C%20this%20is%20the%20home%20of%20Peronism%20%E2%80%93%20and%20its%20economic%20meltdown%20is%20much%20graver%20than%20in%20most%20other%20major%20democracies%2C%20but%20again%20sirens%20are%20ringing.%20Or%20they%20should%20be.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20election%20of%20Donald%20Trump%20in%202016%20was%20a%20huge%20boost%20to%20populism%20around%20the%20world.%20If%20he%20returns%20to%20power%20next%20year%2C%20that%20will%20be%20an%20even%20bigger%20fillip%20to%20the%20far%20right.%20The%20polls%20suggest%20that%20he%20would%20have%20the%20advantage%20in%20a%20rematch%20with%20Joe%20Biden.%20That%E2%80%99s%20in%20spite%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-trump-coup-detat-and-insurrection-was-long-in-the-making-and-will-continue%5C%22%3Ehis%20alleged%20role%20in%20inciting%20what%20many%20regard%20as%20insurrection%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20vehemence%20with%20which%20he%20disputed%20his%20defeat%20in%202020%20without%20any%20substantial%20evidence%20to%20back%20up%20his%20complaints%20of%20election%20fraud.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20afar%2C%20it%20might%20be%20tempting%20to%20smile%20on%20indulgently%20as%20western%20democracy%20threatens%20to%20consume%20itself.%20But%20the%20pandemic%20of%20ultra-nationalism%2C%20racism%2C%20protectionism%20and%20intolerance%20which%20could%20be%20unleashed%20will%20be%20visited%20on%20every%20one%20of%20us.%20That%20genie%20is%20best%20kept%20with%20the%20cork%20tightly%20in%20place.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Ffrino%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Whitehead%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20honorary%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nottingham%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20a%20former%20BBC%20India%20Correspondent.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701159148000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2F12204307%2Funnamed.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-right-wing-is-on-the-rise-globally%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Across%20much%20of%20the%20world%2C%20voters%20are%20turning%20to%20populists%20who%20are%20intensely%20distrustful%20of%20the%20institutions%20on%20which%20liberal%20democracy%20is%20built.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-right-wing-is-on-the-rise-globally%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWon't%20Say%20Again%20And%20Again%26quot%3B%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20Rap%20For%20Delhi%20On%20Rapid%20Rail%20Funds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Fsupreme-court%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20down%20hard%20on%20the%20Delhi%20government%20Tuesday%20over%20delays%20in%20paying%20its%20share%20of%20funds%20-%20around%20Rs%20500%20crore%20-%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Frrts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERegional%20Rapid%20Transit%20System%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20RRTS%2C%20which%20is%20a%20semi-high%20speed%20rail%20corridor%20linking%20to%20Meerut%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Alwar%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Haryana's%20Panipat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProblem%20is%20you%20have%20to%20be%20arm-twisted%20to%20pay%20money%20you%20are%20obligated%20to.%20We%20will%20not%20say%20it%20again%20and%20again.%20Pay%20what%20you%20have%20to...%26quot%3B%20a%20top%20court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20SK%20Kaul%20and%20S%20Dhulia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20government%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-releases-rs-415-crore-for-rapid-rail-project-after-court-warningtransport-minister-kailash-gahlot-4603159%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%20released%20Rs%20415%20crore%20last%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20the%20court%20it%20had%20now%20paid%20all%20its%20dues.%20However%2C%20demanding%20%26quot%3Babsolute%20compliance%26