rted%20in%202020-21.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%2035%20consequential%20train%20accidents%202021-22%2C%20against%2021%20in%202020-21.%20Of%20these%2C%2026%20were%20derailments%20(16%20in%202020-21)%2C%20two%20collisions%20(one%20in%202020-21)%20and%20four%20incidents%20of%20fire%20(three%20in%202020-21).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20causes%20of%20the%20incidents%2C%C2%A0failure%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20railway%20staff%20led%20to%2020%20accidents%20and%20derailments%20rose%20in%202021-22%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ETNIE%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Sixteen%20such%20instances%20were%20reported%20in%202020-21.%20There%20were%20also%20four%20cases%20of%20equipment%20failure%20in%202021-22%2C%20while%20there%20was%20none%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20the%20railways%20paid%20a%20sum%20of%20Rs%2085.88%20crore%20as%20compensation%20under%20Section%20124%20of%20the%20Indian%20Railway%20Act%20for%20death%20or%20injury%20of%20passengers%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20less%20than%20the%20Rs%20104.38%20crore%20it%20paid%20in%202020-21.%20The%20railways%20said%20that%20the%20compensation%20paid%20during%20the%20year%20%E2%80%9Crelates%20to%20the%20number%20of%20cases%20settled%20and%20payment%20made%20during%20the%20year%20and%20not%20necessarily%20to%20the%20accidents%20that%20occurred%20during%20the%20year%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-on-derailments-hard-to-square-with-pmo-claims-on-prioritising-rail-safety%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%E2%80%99s%20analysis%20of%20railway%20accidents%20between%202017%20and%202021%20indicated%20that%20there%20were%202017%20accidents%2C%20Of%20these%2C%20derailments%20accounted%20for%201392%20accidents%2C%20or%2069%25.%20Among%20%E2%80%98consequential%E2%80%99%20train%20accidents%2C